I feel we can create a layer between the actual hashmap and the user function.  In this layer, we keep two offsets, for value and keys. Then before querying the actual map, we correct the key with the key offset, and before return the value, we correct the value with the value offset.

For example:
```
 private Map<Integer, Integer> actualMap;

    private int keyOffset;
    private int valOffset;

    public MyMap() {
        actualMap = new HashMap<>();
        keyOffset = 0;
        valOffset = 0;
    }

    public void incKey(int inc) {
        keyOffset += inc;
    }

    public void incVal(int inc) {
        valOffset += inc;
    }

    public void put(int k, int v) {
        actualMap.put(k - keyOffset, v - valOffset);
    }

    public int get(int k) {
        return actualMap.get(k - keyOffset) + valOffset;
    }
```

